<DOCNO> AP890901-0009 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
the najjar brothers say they 
are victims but fellow villagers call them collaborators they sit 
on the third floor of their firedamaged home cradling uzi 
submachine guns provided by israel 
with the three brothers are several men from other villages who 
joined them in the ruined house after being accused of collaborating 
with the israeli occupation 
many of the 100 palestinians killed by other palestinians in the 
uprising that began nearly 21 months ago were accused of helping 
israel whose soldiers and settlers have killed more than 550 
palestinians 
others of this hilltop towns 10000 residents accuse israel of 
sponsoring a reign of terror they say the najjars and other alleged 
collaborators are guilty of beatings arson random shooting and 
seizing of proplo activists 
they have tear gas sound bombs live bullets everything 
said hamzeh hamarsheh whose son luay a lawyer was hospitalized 
with head wounds after a beating in july they must be removed 
they are a threat to safety 
ziad attatrih 28 who owns a shop that makes aluminumframe 
windows across from the najjar house pointed to eight bullet holes 
in his door 
two weeks ago he said the najjar brothers locked him and his 
workers in the shop and stood guard until israeli soldiers arrived 
and arrested his nephew who was wanted for uprising activities 
later the najjars set fire to his car attatrih said 
they are ruining things but what can we do he said i 
think i will have to move my shop 
hamarsheh said town leaders complained to israeli authorities but 
nothing was done the army says a police investigation began after 
israel television reported on alleged abuses 
the case of yaabad is one of a growing number israeli security 
forces are reported to have increased the arming of palestinian 
collaborators in recent weeks 
palestinians claim the israeli army encourages creation of 
antiplo militias but the military says weapons are given to 
protect threatened palestinians 
shock committees that support the palestine liberation 
organization have been blamed for the deaths of most of the 100 
palestinians killed by others 
col raanan gissin deputy army spokesman said in an interview 
that palestinians were armed on a highly selective casebycase 
basis for selfdefense 
he would not confirm they were collaborators but said the 
palestinians were under strict control with the clear 
understanding that if the weapons are used improperly they have to 
withstand the consequences 
dedi zucker a legislator from the leftwing citizens rights 
movement said in a letter to the defense ministry what is 
happening in yaabad is an illegitimate example of protection being 
given by israel 
arab reporters said at least 40 collaborators had been given 
weapons in this region 45 miles north of jerusalem and several had 
formed the equivalent of militias sometimes operating with israeli 
soldiers 
in habla village the reporters said three collaborators who 
shared a house opened fire to scatter proplo protesters and seized 
boys painting antiisraeli graffiti until soldiers arrived to arrest 
them 
gissin denied the army promoted formation of militias but 
defense minister yitzhak rabin recently said israel would encourage 
palestinians to fight proplo activists 
trouble in yaabad began a year ago when townspeople became 
suspicious that the najjars bassam 35 ali 27 and omar 23 
were colluding with israeli security services they were convinced 
when a najjar sister was seen carrying a pistol which arabs usually 
are forbidden to own 
palestinian activists ordered over loudspeakers that najjars be 
shunned the family business of making aluminum blinds was ruined 
four of their cars were burned and they finally moved away with 
their wives and children 
the house was looted and set afire 
omar najjar standing guard with his uzi on the sootstained top 
floor said his family was wronged and had returned to reclaim its 
rightful place in the community 
i used to be active in the uprising he said i carried the 
palestinian flag in the marches but they turned on us here they 
hounded us even after we moved spreading rumors in our new 
village 
bassam suggested on israeli tv that their relationship with 
israel was official we belong to the shabak shin bet security 
service he said we have orders they told us not to do 
damage we dont they allow us to protect ourselves 
their return coincided with the opening of a military government 
office guarded by several rooftop sentry posts in the village two 
of the posts are within sight of the najjar house which is linked 
to one by a military phone 
</TEXT>
