president bushs meeting at the white house 
today with embattled japanese prime minister toshiki kaifu touches 
off a posthoneymoon foreign policy phase that will test bushs 
management of americas role in the world 
his biggest decisions involve dealing with the soviet union but 
the issues closing in on bush also range from the strenuous effort 
to oust gen manuel antonio noriega from power in panama to the 
intractable arabisraeli dispute and the collapse of a 19nation 
conference on cambodia 
the first seven months in the white house have been relatively 
easy ones for bush his only nearcrisis in foreign policy involved 
the american hostages in lebanon and the slaying of marine lt col 
william higgins 
the hostage problem which also dogged presidents carter and 
reagan was not solved while bush was on vacation in maine but bush 
isnt faced with threatening execution deadlines 
