pave the way for a leftwing coalition in tokyo that bush and his 
conservative followers would findasteful 
the collapse of the paris conference on cambodia means bracing 
for an intensification of the civil war between go that include 
prince sihanouk and the khmer rouge 
the bush administration had hoped the c would produce a 
ceasefire and a transition government now the options are suddenly 
bleak 
in the middle east at some n bush will have to decide whether 
the palestiniberation organization can be coaxed into coope an 
israeli plan for elections on the west bank the president and 
