had not decided whether to appeal gibsons ruling he said senior 
department officials would take a lengthy look at the situation 
which could lead to major changes in the yucca mountain project 
rousso joined the energy department in june 1986 one month 
after leaving science applications and immediately became involved 
in preparing for the yucca mountain bidding process he was chairman 
of a department panel that studied the various yucca mountain 
contract bids and recommended dec 2 that the bechtel team be chosen 
gibson said rousso violated a federal ethics statute that 
prohibits an energy department supervisor from participating in 
department decisions involving any energy company that the 
supervisor has worked for within the past year 
rousso declined to comment on the decision in a brief telephone 
conversation thursday in an interview with the associated press 
earlier this week he said he had acted in good faith and believed 
no conflict of interest had been shown 
the conflictofinterest statute at issue allows for civil 
penalties of up to 10000 for each violation to be imposed by the 
department head or a federal court 
agency spokesman phil keif said he didnt know whether the 
department was considering seeking civil penalties against rousso 
