if he is convicted 
conrad was arrested aug 23 1988 on suspicion of heading a west 
germanbased international spy ring with contacts in sweden and 
vienna austria 
in a statement today federal prosecutor kurt rebmann said conrad 
is charged with grievous treason for providing classified 
material to hungarian military intelligence 
the indictment dated aug 14 has been filed with the superior 
state court in koblenz and also charges conrad with grievous 
treason in working as an agent for the czechoslovak intelligence 
service the statement said 
it said the former soldier provided military documents classified 
as secret and top secret to communist agents including material 
dealing with nuclear operations 
conrad a native of sebring ohio received at least 11 million 
for his work as a spy the statement said 
conrad who retired after 20 years in the military served with 
the army from 1965 to september 1985 and had resided in west germany 
since his discharge 
except for the period september 1979 through november 1980 when 
he was based in the united states conrad served from 1975 until his 
discharge with the us armys 8th infantry division in bad 
kreuznach west germany 
bad kreuznach where conrad continued to live after his 
discharge is about 50 miles west of frankfurt 
the 42yearold conrad was in charge of the divisions classified 
document center during the majority of his time with the unit 
the federal prosecutors statement said conrad was introduced to 
the hungarian secret service in late autumn 1975 by his then 
supervisor in the 8th infantry division who it said also is being 
investigated it did not further identify or provide any other 
information on the supervisor 
the prosecutors office said conrad is suspected of passing 
secrets to the hungarians even after his discharge from the army and 
that he received from the hungarians at least 1 million for his 
work as an agent 
from 1981 through 1986 the suspect also worked for the 
czechoslovak intelligence service to which he also supplied 
photographs of secret military documents conrad received 100000 
from the czechs the statement said 
a date for conrads trial is to be announced later by the koblenz 
superior state court which will hear the case the prosecutors 
office said 
