determined infantry assault for seven days 
world war ii began with the battleships opening salvo on 
westerplatte a polish outpost in then progerman free city of 
danzig at 445 am on sept 1 1939 
at dozens of points along the polish frontier the nazi 
blitzkrieg began without warning a lightningfast panzerled 
invasion by 15 million german troops obliterated the last organized 
polish army units by oct 5 
