antipsychotic drug to a lab for testing in place of its own generic 
version according to a report published today 
however the president of bolar pharmaceutical co of copiague 
ny called the 1982 incident unfortunate and said there was 
no malicious or fraudulent intent 
the washington post reported that bolar on three occasions sent 
brandname mellaril to pharmakinetics laboratory inc for testing 
instead of its generic version of thioridazine 
my technical staff has concluded that the tablets which you set 
for the bioequivalence study are not of your production alan g 
woodman who was president of pharmakinetics said in a letter to 
bolar vice president jack rivers 
excerpts of the letter were published in the post today four 
days after the food and drug administration proposed removing from 
the market bolars generic version of dyazide a drug for treating 
high blood pressure 
the fda said it has not been able to fully establish that 
bolars generic version is as effective as dyazide 
meantime bolar employees took out a fullpage advertisement in 
