in his first two months in office 
president carlos menem has imposed drastic measures on argentines to 
bring their chaotic economy back into line and he is winning their 
support 
he has more than tripled prices for public services 
electricity gas and water rates subway bus and train fares and 
has temporarily shored up an economy that had set off food riots and 
forced the radical civic unions raul alfonsin out of the presidency 
22 weeks before his term was up 
and while one of every two argentines did not vote for menem the 
peronist in mays presidential election he now is gaining favor 
for what he has done so far 
