year for many the credit ratings of many of the major money center 
banks also were lowered 
the moodys report released wednesday said more steps may be 
needed because the third world debt problem appears to be 
unraveling further 
they us banks are not all out of the woods yet it said 
the extent to which banks need to pad their loanloss reserves 
remains in dispute 
last spring the general accounting office the auditing arm of 
congress said third world countries were falling behind on 70 
billion in debt repayments to us banks and that american 
regulators should make banks put up more reserves to protect 
depositors against loan losses 
but more recently the us comptroller of the currency 
