amount to nearly half of their credits to troubled debtor nations 
up from around a third the us average is 30 percent 
the moodys report said the us plan for reducing the 13 
trillion third world debt known as the brady plan has begun an 
irreversible process of forgiveness the debt initiative places 
more emphasis on having lender banks cut debt and interest payments 
than on providing new loans 
the us government has shifted from one focused on protecting 
the banks to one focused on protecting the political and 
economic stability of the borrowers by encouraging debt reduction 
the report said 
mexico in july became the first nation to reach a debt 
restructuring agreement under the brady plan although a number of 
its creditor banks reportedly have been slow to participate in the 
plan 
