nations biggest retailers announced their august sales results 
consumers generally are in a strong financial position and are 
confident right now but their spending is drifting sideways 
agreed jeffrey edelman an analyst with drexel burnham lambert inc 
consumers have cut back on purchases of what are called 
discretionary items as opposed to necessities such as food because 
of rising mortgage payments and other credit costs 
august sales are important because the month marks the beginning 
of the retailers most critical season shopping generally 
accelerates in midaugust as families prepare for the new school 
year and then continues to build through the holiday season when 
stores earn about half their annual profits 
economists track retail sales because the figures are a component 
consumer spending which in turn accounts for about twothirds of 
us economic activity 
