fujisawa pharmaceutical co announced friday it is 
acquiring lyphomed inc for about 670 million the first major 
acquisition of a us drug company by a japanese pharmaceutical 
maker 
we believe the merger of lyphomed and our us operations will 
further strengthen our position in the us and will allow fujisawa 
to compete more effectively in world markets dr tomokichiro 
fujisawa president of the osaka japanbased company said in a 
statement released by the two companies 
fujisawa has owned nearly 30 percent of lyphomed about 9 
million of the companys 299 million common shares since october 
1986 according to lyphomed spokeswoman melissa marsden 
the 3187ashare purchase price exceeds fujisawas 31ashare 
offer last week for lyphomed based in the chicago suburb of 
rosemont the final figure represents an alltime high for lyphomed 
shares which are traded over the counter 
ms marsden put the purchase price at approximately 670 million 
which includes conversion of the companys preferred stock 
the merger should be completed april 1 the companies said 
dr john n kapoor lyphomeds chairman said the new merged 
organization has the potential to be a worldwide leader 
we eagerly anticipate building on our past achievements and 
contributing lyphomeds many talents as part of fujisawas team 
kapoor said in the statement 
kapoor owns about 14 percent of lyphomeds stock a stake he had 
previously agreed to sell to fujisawa once lyphomeds board approved 
a buyout 
this is the first major acquisition ever of a us drug company 
by a japanese drug company said john boettiger first vice 
president of rotanmosle inc a houston securities firm i think 
its a good deal for both companies 
fujisawa sells pills primarily and lyphomed is the largest 
provider of intravenous drugs to hospitals boettiger said 
the buzz word in health care is combination therapy and this 
allows either company to provide both intravenous and oral 
medicine 
fujisawa is the largest researchbased drug company in japan 
boettiger said its sales for the fiscal year ended march 1 were 
146 billion 
the deal will give fujisawa access to lyphomeds us sales 
network which already markets about 400 products to more than 95 
percent of us hospitals he said 
