operations but other activities such as refining were not 
affected 
he said no figures were immediately available on absenteeism 
the strikers are protesting a decision by the governments copper 
company codelco to add 412 miners to 300 already under a work 
schedule known as continued week which means they would would 
take their day off on weekdays instead of sunday 
the company said the measure is needed to ensure that the mine 
will remain in operation every day of the year 
according to the chilean labor law a legal strike can not last 
longer than 59 days 
new efforts to settle the strike were reported under way friday 
union leader bustamente said the mining ministry could soon start a 
mediation effort 
