<TEXT>
the food and drug administration said friday it 
is investigating a 1982 incident in which the maker of a generic 
version of an antipsychotic drug substituted samples of another 
companys brandname version for testing 
the incident involved bolar pharmaceutical co inc of copiague 
ny one of 11 companies being investigated by the fda for problems 
ranging from manufacturing irregularities to fraud the company is 
one of the nations largest drug manufacturers 
the disclosure came less than a week after the fda began steps to 
remove from the market bolars version of the hypertension drug 
dyazide the agency said its investigation has been unable to 
determine whether the generic version is as effective as the 
brandname product 
bolar issued a statement saying that its version of the drug 
thioridazine was never developed never tested never sent to the 
fda and never marketed 
bolar president robert shulman was quoted in fridays wall street 
journal and washington post as saying the incident was a 
manufacturing error and an isolated case that occurred in 
attempting to copy the tablet color of the brandname drug 
fda spokesman jeff nesbit said we have additional bolar drugs 
under investigation including thioridazine 
in the course of the fdas investigation the agency obtained a 
letter from pharmakinetics laboratories inc of baltimore to bolar 
questioning based on a visual inspection the thioridazine samples 
bolar submitted for testing the brandname version of the drug 
mellaril is made by sandoz ltd 
pharmakinetics officials became suspicious that bolar was 
switching samples after the outer coating of tablets sent for 
testing began to chip and the sandoz logo became visible 
bolar later submitted different generic versions of mellaril and 
won fda approval to market the product in 1983 the approved pills 
were a different size shape and weight from the brandname drug 
paul perito an attorney for pharmakinetics called the bolar 
matter an isolated incident pharmakinetics president steven 
woodman added we have not had any other incident like this from 
this manufacturer or any other 
earlier this summer vitarine pharmaceuticals inc of spring 
valley ny admitted to the fda that it substituted a brandname 
product for its generic version to win fda approval 
pharmakinetics did the testing for that drug as well but woodman 
said the lab did not suspect any problems at the time 
in the case of bolars generic version of mellaril 
pharmakinetics said it notified the company of the problem after it 
was noticed and refused to conduct tests on the samples 
pharmakinetics is not the keeper of morality in the 
pharmaceutical industry alan g woodman who was president of 
pharmakinetics at the time said to bolar vice president jack rivers 
in a letter obtained by the post 
but jack you are an important part of an american success 
story and its our opinion that the exposure you place yourself and 
your company by pursuing this course of action far outweighs any 
possible benefit which may accrue to you or the company 
pharmakinetics was not required to notify the fda of the problem 
pharmakinetics and fda officials said 
bolar in its statement said the letter appeared to have been 
leaked to the news media to increase pressure on the fda to remove 
lowcost generic dyazide from the marketplace 
in a fullpage advertisement in fridays new york times bolar 
employees stated their support for their companys management and 
said they were outraged at us rep john dingell dmich 
chairman of the energy and commerce investigations subcommittee 
which has been investigating the generic drug industry and fdas 
generic drug division 
the ad attacked dingell for creating a climate of fear and 
distrust within the entire generic pharmaceutical industry because 
of the fraudulent deeds of a few 
</TEXT>
